fields.eventdetails: On September 26 2021 at approximately 4am, a customer came to the pay window and attempted to purchase a lighter. The customer became agitated when the GSA told him the price and proceeded to verbally abuse the GSA. He then went around the building and attempted to break in through the carwash door. Door was secured so he was unable to do so and left. On September 27th 2021 at approximately 3am, the customer returned wielding a knife. He walked up to the pay window again and scratched the surface of the window. The GSA then locked himself in the office and called the police. Police were already on the property, responding to another call, and had witnessed the event. During this time the customer used his knife to puncture several bottles of oil. The police responded by making him pay for the damaged product and arresting the customer. The GSA informed the manager of the incident once police made their presence known.
fields.actionstaken: Police called and security standards reviewed.
fields.correctiveactions: No corrective action taken. GSA followed security protocols and protected himself and property as much as possible.
